What are the basic definition of global
warming and climate change.
“Global warming” refers to the rise in global temperatures
due mainly to the increasing concentrations of greenhouse
gases in the atmosphere.
“Climate change” refers to the increasing changes in the
measures of climate over a long period of time –including
precipitation, temperature, and wind patterns.
How the UAE and Malaysia are contributing to
help with this issue
Malaysia’s solar farm on water
UAE’s contribution
The UAE announced its focus on adopting climate-smart
agricultural practices, including organic and hydroponic farming,
new technologies and climate-adaptive crops, in order to reduce
emissions from the sector. 2021: The UAE launched the Food
Tech Valley project that is currently under development in Dubai.
UAE’s COP 28
To put it simply, the COP is where the world comes together to agree on ways
to address the climate crisis, such as limiting global temperature rise to 1.5
degrees Celsius, helping vulnerable communities adapt to the effects of
climate change, and achieving net-zero emissions by 2050.
December 2023.
At COP28, there was a collective effort leading to significant achievements. Loss and
damage were addressed through operationalization, and substantial funds were allocated.
Over $85 billion in new financial commitments were mobilized. ALTÉRRA, the world's
largest private investor focusing on climate change solutions, was launched. Numerous
milestones were achieved, including a global goal to triple renewables and double energy
efficiency, declarations on agriculture, food, and health, and increased commitment from
oil and gas companies on methane and emissions. The final agreement includes language
specifically addressing fossil fuels, marking several world firsts in these accomplishments,
as summarized by COP28 President Dr. Sultan Al Jaber.
COP28
What are the 4 pillars of COP28
The key outcomes of global climate action across the four
pillars set by the COP 28 Presidency:
i) fast-tracking a just, orderly, and equitable energy
transition
ii) fixing climate finance
iii) focusing on people, lives and livelihoods
iv) underpinning everything with full inclusivity
Conclusion about COP28
The accountable implementation of the myriad of actions
showcased, involving the collaboration between multiple
actors across the global climate action agenda, could
significantly contribute towards correcting the course and
achieving climate action targets in this decisive decade.
Before getting to Malaysian solar
panels
●We must know how solar panels work.
●When the sun shines onto a solar panel,
energy from the sunlight is absorbed
by the PV cells in the panel. This energy
creates electrical charges that move in
response to an internal electrical field in
the cell, causing electricity to flow.
Malaysian water solar farms
●Malaysian state-owned TNB has launched a tender
for the development of a 30 MW (AC) floating solar
project at Chenderoh Reservoir in the country’s east.
●According to tender documents, developers have
until Dec. 8, 2023, to submit their proposals for the
engineering, procurement, construction and
commissioning (EPCC) of the plant, which will be built
at one of Malaysia’s major hydroelectric dams.
●The Southeast Asian country aims to generate 30% of
its energy from renewables by 2030, according to the
most recent government master plan.
●
You may ask… How do solar panels help with
global warming?
Generating electricity from solar panels produce
no greenhouse gases whatsoever, and so can help
to reduce the effect of climate change if used
widely.
Here are three important ideas relating solar
energy and chemistry.
Solar cells convert light into electricity, utilizing a material sandwiched between metal plates. The selection of this
material is critical, as it determines the efficiency of energy capture. The energy gap between the valence and
conduction bands is key; when photons hit electrons, they jump from the valence to the conduction band,
generating electricity. Chemistry and electroplating advancements contribute by optimizing semiconductor
properties, reducing energy gaps for improved efficiency. Electroplating techniques further enhance metal
components' conductivity, ensuring sustainable and efficient energy conversion in solar cells. This
interdisciplinary approach underscores the importance of materials science, chemistry, and electroplating in
advancing solar cell technologies.
